I was on the phone with a blogger who was
gleefully going on about your heart attack

27:00.420 --> 27:01.830
Kevin.

27:04.220 --> 27:05.910
I was trying to protect you. I'm sorry.

27:06.010 --> 27:06.990
I thought that was my job.

27:07.100 --> 27:09.170
Your job is to stay on message.

27:09.270 --> 27:10.720
This campaign has an identity.

27:10.830 --> 27:12.350
It is supposed to be about something.

27:12.450 --> 27:14.400
I was very clear how I felt about that.

27:14.490 --> 27:15.690
But you didn't tell me not to do it.

27:15.780 --> 27:19.120
You were very high minded and
noble, but you didn't say that.

27:19.210 --> 27:20.700
You left a window wide open for me.

27:20.810 --> 27:21.580
I mean, come on.

27:21.700 --> 27:24.730
Travis took it upon himself to play "hardball"?

27:24.840 --> 27:26.340
You were practically asking me to do it.

27:26.440 --> 27:29.400
All right, even if that were true, and
my impulse control was that far off,

27:29.500 --> 27:30.820
I look to you to be my compass.

27:30.920 --> 27:32.120
I need you to pull me back.

27:32.230 --> 27:34.260
I need to be able to trust that.

27:34.330 --> 27:37.660
Okay, you guys need to stop.

27:37.750 --> 27:39.430
- No, we're just we're just in the middle of something.
- No, no, no. I'm sorry.

27:39.530 --> 27:41.120
But, Kevin, you... you have to leave.

27:41.230 --> 27:42.210
- No, he doesn't.
- Yes, he does.

27:42.320 --> 27:43.590
- No, Kevin. Stay.
- No, Kevin. Go.

27:43.690 --> 27:46.280
Well, this is now turning
into my worst nightmare.

27:46.400 --> 27:47.920
Sister trumps boss.

27:48.000 --> 27:49.230
You have to go.

27:50.020 --> 27:50.870
Go.

27:51.370 --> 27:53.110
- You sure?
- Fine.

27:54.600 --> 27:55.530
Sorry.

27:58.710 --> 27:59.680
Are you.

28:00.650 --> 28:02.220
What the hell are you doing?

28:02.350 --> 28:03.390
I need ten minutes with him.

28:03.490 --> 28:05.420
I am in the middle of a crisis.

28:05.500 --> 28:06.750
I have cancer.

28:09.740 --> 28:11.090
I have lymphoma.

28:11.190 --> 28:15.600
It's the bad kind. Diffuse large B-cell.

28:15.920 --> 28:19.790
- What doctor have you...
- I have been to the oncologist twice.

28:19.900 --> 28:21.910
And I have a...

28:22.390 --> 28:24.820
a bone marrow biopsy
scheduled for tomorrow.

28:24.930 --> 28:28.190
- Okay, come and sit down.
- No, no, I... I don't.

28:28.560 --> 28:31.200
I don't want to sit down.

28:31.320 --> 28:32.300
We just need to talk about this.

28:32.410 --> 28:34.010
I don't want to talk.

28:35.700 --> 28:37.640
I don't want to talk.

28:46.030 --> 28:48.490
Rebecca, where are the financials?

28:48.610 --> 28:49.410
I put them in your desk.

28:49.520 --> 28:51.260
Well, they're not there.

28:51.380 --> 28:52.920
I'm sure I put them there. Did you move them?

28:53.020 --> 28:56.130
How could I move them if you didn't
put them back in the first place?

28:56.230 --> 28:57.530
Okay, well, do you have another copy?

28:57.640 --> 28:58.310
No, no, Rebecca.

28:58.420 --> 29:00.610
We don't have another copy.

29:00.720 --> 29:04.300
That document is our account
numbers, it lists all our assets,

29:04.410 --> 29:08.250
everything that we've had to scramble
around thanks to Tommy's mess.

29:08.350 --> 29:09.850
Oh, they're right here.

29:10.440 --> 29:11.230
Oh, thank God.

29:11.430 --> 29:13.060
That's so weird. I'm sure I put them in there.

29:13.160 --> 29:13.740
I... I'm sorry.

29:13.860 --> 29:15.930
I just I have so much stress.

29:16.020 --> 29:18.040
Things have gotten so rough around here.

29:18.140 --> 29:20.420
I... I'm sorry if I snapped at you.

29:20.530 --> 29:21.210
No, no, it's fine.

29:21.330 --> 29:23.710
I don't want any special treatment.

29:23.800 --> 29:26.230
I hope that's not why you chose my pitch.

29:26.340 --> 29:26.970
What?

29:27.080 --> 29:28.310
'Cause I'm your daughter?

29:28.390 --> 29:29.370
No, Rebecca.

29:29.470 --> 29:30.930
I wouldn't do that.

29:31.040 --> 29:35.420
I chose your idea because
your idea was the best idea.

29:36.450 --> 29:38.410
You earned it.

29:39.340 --> 29:40.630
Thank you.

29:40.980 --> 29:41.750
I gotta go.

29:41.870 --> 29:42.860
Where are you going?

29:43.000 --> 29:44.060
Back to work.

29:52.270 --> 29:53.610
Uh, I'm sorry I'm late.

29:53.740 --> 29:56.470
- But the traffic was...
- Did you bring what I asked for?

29:56.580 --> 29:57.520
Uh, yeah.

29:58.650 --> 30:01.120
I made the copies like you said.

30:02.270 --> 30:03.690
Oh, and I don't know if this matters or not,

30:03.800 --> 30:08.980
but I know they're gonna start making cheap wine
and buying bulk juice from other vineyards.

30:09.070 --> 30:10.580
Yeah, it matters.

30:13.060 --> 30:16.250
How long did you know William Walker?

30:17.590 --> 30:19.240
A long time.

30:20.190 --> 30:22.780
What'd you say you needed those for again?

30:23.160 --> 30:24.090
You have your reasons.

30:24.220 --> 30:25.360
I have mine.

30:31.920 --> 30:33.310
I was still reading that.

30:33.520 --> 30:34.420
Okay.

30:34.830 --> 30:36.150
I'm still drinking that.

30:36.520 --> 30:38.640
Please. This has to stop, okay?

30:38.740 --> 30:39.420
You're still mad.

30:39.520 --> 30:40.080
I get it.

30:40.210 --> 30:43.600
No, I'm thirsty and I haven't finished
reading the newspaper.

30:43.700 --> 30:46.650
I... I shouldn't have left you at mom's.

30:46.750 --> 30:49.430
I'm sorry. Look, why don't I
just, I'll... I'll pay the cab fare.

30:49.540 --> 30:50.440
Call it retribution.

30:50.550 --> 30:51.840
It's not about the cab, Kevin.

30:51.940 --> 30:54.840
I'm not gonna force babies
on you ever again okay?

30:54.940 --> 30:56.720
I'm not gonna force anything on anybody.

30:56.810 --> 30:59.560
You should've heard Robert last night.

30:59.690 --> 31:02.570
I'll be lucky if I still have a job when I go in today.

31:02.810 --> 31:04.430
You're always going to have a job, Kevin.

31:04.540 --> 31:05.870
You live for it.

31:07.610 --> 31:14.310
And you say you want a baby, and I'm sure you do,
but who's gonna be at home to look after it?

31:14.410 --> 31:15.410
I mean.

31:15.800 --> 31:17.940
I have a life, too, and it may
not be as important as yours,

31:18.040 --> 31:19.320
it may not be in the newspaper every day,

31:19.420 --> 31:21.990
but I like what I do, and I'm not
sure I'm ready to give that up yet.

31:22.090 --> 31:23.250
I'm... I'm not asking you to.

31:23.350 --> 31:24.400
Yes, you are.

31:24.510 --> 31:26.280
By the way you live your life, you are.

31:26.380 --> 31:27.230
I mean, look at your hours.

31:27.350 --> 31:31.210
The campaign has barely even started, and what
happens when you're on the road campaigning?

31:31.330 --> 31:32.610
We can get a nanny.

31:32.730 --> 31:35.850
That still doesn't change the fact
that you're never gonna be around.

31:36.360 --> 31:38.640
I'm not gonna be an absent father.

31:39.000 --> 31:39.900
I grew up with one.

31:40.020 --> 31:42.980
That's not what I want for my child.

31:43.990 --> 31:45.190
Okay.

31:45.680 --> 31:48.020
Then promise me if things get
crazy, you'll quit your job.

31:48.120 --> 31:49.610
Promise me that.

31:53.450 --> 31:55.670
I can't do that.

31:59.230 --> 32:04.980
But what I can do is try to prove to you...

32:05.110 --> 32:06.760
as much as possible that.

32:06.880 --> 32:14.930
I will try my best to do what's right what...
whatever that is for us and for our kid.

32:15.050 --> 32:18.950
Every family has these doubts, but...

32:19.240 --> 32:21.860
you just have to make a leap of faith.

32:23.220 --> 32:26.430
I just want to make sure we leap together.

32:27.910 --> 32:29.260
We will.

32:29.390 --> 32:31.100
I promise.

32:34.240 --> 32:37.390
The cab cost $32. 50.

32:37.520 --> 32:42.710
But...  I know how you can pay me back.

32:43.520 --> 32:46.970
So... does this mean you're
in love with me again?

32:47.060 --> 32:49.940
I never stopped loving you, Kevin.

32:58.740 --> 33:00.140
Kitty.

33:07.260 --> 33:09.300
- Can I get you anything?
- No, no.

33:09.410 --> 33:14.960
I am not supposed to eat or drink anything for
12 hours before my bone marrow biopsy.

33:15.090 --> 33:16.130
Okay.

33:16.320 --> 33:17.360
I'll be right in here.

33:17.460 --> 33:18.060
Okay.

33:18.260 --> 33:24.260
Robert, I... I think I'm ready to talk.

33:24.500 --> 33:25.350
Oh, honey.

33:25.490 --> 33:26.610
No, I know.

33:26.730 --> 33:28.430
No, I don't think you do.

33:30.120 --> 33:32.820
And even if you do, I need to say it.

33:34.800 --> 33:39.560
We are going to fight this, and we are
going to go wherever we have to go,

33:39.680 --> 33:43.970
see whoever we have to see,
and we are gonna win.

33:44.080 --> 33:47.270
'Cause I'm not gonna let
anything happen to you.

33:49.380 --> 33:52.160
I just can't believe that you've been
carrying all this around inside of you.

33:52.280 --> 33:53.690
Why didn't you tell me?

33:55.710 --> 33:56.670
I know. I know.

33:56.790 --> 33:58.690
I think I was just...

33:58.800 --> 33:59.940
scared.

34:00.040 --> 34:01.900
But why?

34:02.350 --> 34:03.860
Because I....

34:03.990 --> 34:07.970
was afraid that you wouldn't
be there for me.

34:08.080 --> 34:10.239
Of course I'm here for you.

34:10.370 --> 34:11.510
Well.

34:12.540 --> 34:15.480
Maybe I was afraid of that, too.

34:15.560 --> 34:17.800
I... I don't understand.

34:19.850 --> 34:21.270
Well.

34:22.909 --> 34:26.650
What if you're only here
because I have cancer?

34:31.790 --> 34:33.920
- I am here because I love you.
- Oh, God.

34:34.070 --> 34:35.679
I want to believe that.

34:36.449 --> 34:39.949
I so want to believe that. I do.

34:40.070 --> 34:41.360
I do.

34:51.050 --> 34:52.870
Look how cute you are.

34:52.889 --> 34:54.300
Hey, how are you?

34:54.409 --> 34:55.699
I'm good.

34:55.840 --> 34:59.350
Just, uh, taking a break, finally.

34:59.450 --> 35:01.250
Well, I am not.

35:01.390 --> 35:02.960
Ooh, you're not?

35:04.800 --> 35:07.350
What? I finally have more to do around here.

35:07.470 --> 35:09.010
I asked my mom for more work.

35:09.110 --> 35:10.770
And guess what.

35:10.880 --> 35:11.450
I got it.

35:11.590 --> 35:12.660
Well, that's... that's great.

35:12.780 --> 35:13.900
What do I get?

35:14.030 --> 35:14.950
You get to wait.

35:15.060 --> 35:16.340
- To wait?
- Yes.

35:16.450 --> 35:18.430
But I can't wait.

35:18.610 --> 35:19.940
Sorry. It's freaky Friday.

35:20.040 --> 35:22.030
I love freaky Fridays.

35:23.050 --> 35:24.700
Okay, fine. But I have to get this done.

35:24.800 --> 35:26.240
I can't just fall asleep after.

35:26.340 --> 35:27.940
I would never ask you to do that.

35:28.040 --> 35:29.170
I'm probably gonna fall asleep after.

35:29.310 --> 35:30.910
I'll tell you that right now.

35:31.000 --> 35:33.600
I'm only here because the Governor made me come.

35:33.750 --> 35:35.330
So say it.

35:36.610 --> 35:38.530
You have to.

35:40.300 --> 35:41.220
I went behind her back.

35:41.330 --> 35:43.070
She had nothing to do with the leak.

35:44.360 --> 35:46.120
And?

35:53.480 --> 35:55.090
I'm sorry.

35:55.900 --> 35:57.120
All right.

35:59.710 --> 36:01.490
Now it's your turn.

36:03.630 --> 36:05.870
Well, yeah, well, yeah, well, I'm yeah, I'm sorry.

36:05.990 --> 36:06.870
No, no. Not good enough.

36:06.990 --> 36:09.490
Say it louder.

36:13.950 --> 36:16.890
It was, uh.

36:16.990 --> 36:19.560
Yeah, it was... it was my idea to....

36:19.790 --> 36:24.300
leak your boss' affair, and I'm sorry.

36:26.750 --> 36:30.620
You know, you do realize, when this is
all over, we could be very good friends?

36:30.740 --> 36:32.810
We're cut from the same cloth.

36:33.310 --> 36:34.740
And what is that?

36:35.040 --> 36:37.560
Oh, cynical, meretricious, mercenary...

36:37.850 --> 36:38.860
God. You're killing me.

36:38.970 --> 36:40.340
Travis.

36:41.170 --> 36:43.010
Do I have something to worry about?

36:43.140 --> 36:44.480
Nope. Just paying my respects.

36:44.600 --> 36:48.050
It, uh, still looks good around here.

36:48.130 --> 36:48.750
Goodbye.

36:48.870 --> 36:49.920
Goodbye.

36:52.800 --> 36:53.570
What's going on?

36:53.690 --> 36:58.020
D... do you think I'm like him?

36:58.140 --> 36:59.210
I don't know.

36:59.330 --> 37:00.300
Maybe.

37:00.740 --> 37:02.190
I mean, I don't know.

37:02.720 --> 37:04.100
You and I have different jobs.

37:04.210 --> 37:08.330
You were trying to protect me, and for the
record, if somebody was coming after you,

37:08.440 --> 37:09.350
I'd rip their head off.

37:09.450 --> 37:10.980
I'd have done the same thing.

37:11.300 --> 37:13.880
Great. Uh, you have a television interview,

37:14.000 --> 37:15.270
so we should probably head over there.

37:15.370 --> 37:16.290
I'm just gonna go alone.

37:16.400 --> 37:17.860
You... you want me to stay here?

37:17.980 --> 37:19.690
Yeah. I got it.

37:19.800 --> 37:21.850
We're... we are good, right?

37:21.970 --> 37:22.830
Yeah.

37:23.280 --> 37:24.570
We're good.

37:29.210 --> 37:34.770
As you now know, I did have a
heart attack a few months ago.

37:34.900 --> 37:38.760
Ironically, it was the same
day that my son was born.

37:38.900 --> 37:45.120
And, uh, how my wife Kitty
managed that day, I'll never know.

37:46.360 --> 37:47.880
Dr. Avadon should be right in.

37:47.990 --> 37:48.900
Okay.

37:49.170 --> 37:52.300
Kitty was completely there for me and Evan.

37:52.420 --> 37:53.400
Here's a gown for you to put on.

37:53.500 --> 37:56.060
And, uh, let me tell you something, I was scared.

37:56.190 --> 38:01.390
You know, to face your
own mortality is frightening.

38:09.420 --> 38:10.370
How you doing?

38:10.580 --> 38:11.750
I'm good as...

38:11.850 --> 38:14.150
as long as I don't look over there.

38:14.330 --> 38:15.130
Well, you know what?

38:15.250 --> 38:17.640
Why don't you look right here?

38:17.970 --> 38:18.840
Oh, my God.

38:18.980 --> 38:21.440
- Is that a banana nut?
- It is.

38:21.560 --> 38:25.740
And the minute this is all over with, it's all yours.

38:27.560 --> 38:28.530
Okay.

38:28.970 --> 38:30.870
Let's get you guys out of here.

38:30.990 --> 38:32.240
Okay...

38:34.450 --> 38:39.400
so if I misled the people of
California, I also misled myself.

38:39.520 --> 38:41.290
I'm not proud of it.

38:41.390 --> 38:47.520
But I think that it takes time before
you can talk about something like this.

38:47.630 --> 38:49.540
You're gonna feel a little pressure.

38:50.700 --> 38:52.740
You need to find the courage.

38:55.020 --> 38:58.930
And when you do talk, you realize.

38:59.050 --> 39:05.980
The most amazing thing that what's
happening, as... as horrible as it is.

39:06.100 --> 39:10.190
Is bringing you closer to the people that you love.

39:10.500 --> 39:15.520
It's reminding you of what's most true in your life.

39:17.600 --> 39:19.830
And that is a good thing.

39:19.940 --> 39:21.480
All done.

39:24.700 --> 39:27.780
No matter how it happens.

39:38.550 --> 39:40.130
Nora?

39:41.610 --> 39:43.520
Nora, what are you doing here?

39:43.640 --> 39:46.360
I dropped Evan off early this morning,
and I thought I'd come find you.

39:46.460 --> 39:47.860
I know you walk here every day.

39:47.960 --> 39:51.550
So if you came here to apologize, Nora,
you didn't have to come this far.

39:51.670 --> 39:53.430
You could've just called me on the phone.

39:53.530 --> 39:55.330
I wanted to do it in person.

39:55.420 --> 39:56.100
Thank you.

39:56.210 --> 39:57.600
Apology accepted.

39:59.220 --> 40:01.500
My God, it's beautiful here.

40:03.080 --> 40:04.370
Maybe I should.

40:04.480 --> 40:07.410
Walk with you every day, and it would make me.

40:07.540 --> 40:09.650
Strong and calm.

40:09.740 --> 40:10.750
That would be good.

40:10.860 --> 40:12.850
I could use the company.

40:14.790 --> 40:17.770
I'm so tired of.

40:18.170 --> 40:21.160
trying to make sure everybody does the right thing.

40:21.280 --> 40:23.440
I don't know what the right thing is myself.

40:23.560 --> 40:25.640
By everybody, what are you
talking about, the children?

40:25.750 --> 40:28.140
Yes. Why do I have to have
the answers all the time?

40:28.240 --> 40:29.320
I don't have the answers.

40:29.430 --> 40:30.460
I can't be calm.

40:30.560 --> 40:31.180
I can't be strong.

40:31.310 --> 40:32.370
Nora, you don't have to be calm.

40:32.480 --> 40:33.370
You don't have to be strong.

40:33.480 --> 40:34.570
Come on.

40:35.000 --> 40:36.990
- Kitty's sick.
- What?

40:37.120 --> 40:39.170
What do you mean, "sick"?W hat kind of sick?

40:39.300 --> 40:41.380
Oh, she doesn't want me to tell you this.

40:41.490 --> 40:43.340
- I shouldn't be saying anything.
- Nora, tell me.

40:43.450 --> 40:45.500
I'm your brother. It's me.

40:47.850 --> 40:49.340
It's cancer.

40:49.460 --> 40:51.550
- She's got cancer.
- Oh, God.

40:51.670 --> 40:53.050
It should be me, Saul.

40:53.170 --> 40:54.110
It should be me.

40:54.250 --> 40:55.010
I'm old.

40:55.170 --> 40:57.140
She's so young and she has a little baby.

40:57.330 --> 40:58.550
Is she getting treatment?

40:58.710 --> 41:00.570
- Yes. - Good.

41:01.190 --> 41:03.380
I don't want her to have to do this.

41:03.610 --> 41:06.160
I don't want her to have to do this.

41:06.300 --> 41:07.680
I don't want her to have to do this.

41:07.880 --> 41:09.200
Oh, it's okay.

41:11.320 --> 41:13.330
It's okay. It's okay.

